---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Pullquote from '../../components/Pullquote.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Daily" description="Readings, reflections, and prayers tied to the liturgical calendar.">

  <!-- Daily Hero -->
  <div class="daily-page-hero">
    <div class="container--narrow">
      <div class="daily-page-date">Today's Liturgical Day</div>
      <h1 class="daily-page-feast">Wednesday of Bright Week</h1>
      <div class="daily-page-tone">Tone 1 · Paschal Season · No Fast</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container--narrow" style="padding-bottom:80px;">

    <!-- Paschal Troparion -->
    <div class="daily-section">
      <div class="daily-section-label">Paschal Troparion</div>
      <p class="daily-prayer-text">
        Christ is risen from the dead,<br />
        trampling down death by death,<br />
        and upon those in the tombs<br />
        bestowing life.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Scripture -->
    <div class="daily-section">
      <div class="daily-section-label">Scripture Readings</div>
      <div class="reading-block">
        <div class="reading-type">Epistle</div>
        <div class="reading-ref">Acts 2:22–36</div>
        <p class="reading-excerpt">"This Jesus God raised up, and of that we all are witnesses…"</p>
      </div>
      <div class="reading-block" style="margin-top:20px;">
        <div class="reading-type">Gospel</div>
        <div class="reading-ref">John 1:35–51</div>
        <p class="reading-excerpt">"Come and see."</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Reflection -->
    <div class="daily-section">
      <div class="daily-section-label">Reflection</div>
      <p>The first disciples didn't receive a theology lesson. They received an invitation: <em>Come and see.</em> Andrew and John didn't follow Jesus because they were convinced by an argument. They followed because something in his presence pulled them forward.</p>
      <p style="margin-top:16px;">The Paschal season is an invitation to the same encounter. Not to learn <em>about</em> the Resurrection, but to stand inside it. Christ is risen. Come and see.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Desert Father -->
    <div class="daily-section">
      <div class="daily-section-label">Desert Father</div>
      <Pullquote attribution="— The Sayings of the Desert Fathers (Alphabetical Collection)">
        "A brother asked Abba Moses for a word. The old man said: Go and sit in your cell, and your cell will teach you everything."
      </Pullquote>
      <p class="desert-father-note">Abba Moses was a 4th-century Egyptian monk, a former bandit who became one of the most revered Desert Fathers. His counsel here is deceptively simple: stop looking for answers outside. Sit still. The silence will do the rest.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Prayer -->
    <div class="daily-section">
      <div class="daily-section-label">Prayer</div>
      <p class="daily-prayer-text">
        O Heavenly King, Comforter, Spirit of Truth,<br />
        who are everywhere present and fill all things,<br />
        Treasury of blessings and Giver of Life,<br />
        come and dwell in us,<br />
        cleanse us from every stain,<br />
        and save our souls, O gracious Lord.
      </p>
      <div class="prayer-source">Prayer to the Holy Spirit — from the Horologion</div>
    </div>

  </div>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .daily-page-hero {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 56px 0 40px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .daily-page-hero::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: radial-gradient(ellipse at 50% 40%, rgba(186,143,67,0.08) 0%, transparent 60%);
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .daily-page-date {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--censer-smoke);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .daily-page-feast {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 30px;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--beeswax);
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .daily-page-tone {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--deep-muted);
    position: relative;
  }
  .daily-section {
    background: var(--warm-dark);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }
  .daily-section-label {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--halo-gold);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
  }
  .daily-section-label::after {
    content: '';
    flex: 1;
    height: 0.5px;
    background: var(--gold-15);
  }
  .daily-prayer-text {
    text-align: center;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 19px;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--beeswax);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .reading-type {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--halo-gold);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .reading-ref {
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--beeswax);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .reading-excerpt {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--censer-smoke);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .desert-father-note {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--censer-smoke);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-top: 12px;
  }
  .prayer-source {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--deep-muted);
    margin-top: 8px;
    text-align: center;
  }
</style>
